body:
> Verilator version
```
Verilator 4.038 2020-07-11 rev v4.036-114-g0cd4a57ad
```
> Testcase
```systemverilog
// t_module_err.v
module t (/*AUTOARG*/
   clk
   );

   input clk;
   wire           a, b, x;

   A mod_a(
           .x                           (x),
           .clk                         (clk),
           .a                           (a),
           .b                           (b));
   always @ (posedge clk) begin 
       $display("Hello World"); 
       $finish; 
   end
endmodule

module A(/*AUTOARG*/
   x,
   clk, a, b
   );
   
   input clk;
   input a, b;
   output x;
   wire   y, c;
   
   B mod_b(
           .y                           (y),
           .b                           (b),
           .c                           (c));

   C mod_c(
           .x                           (x),
           .clk                         (clk),
           .a                           (a),
           .y                           (y));
endmodule

module B(/*AUTOARG*/
   y,
   b, c
   );
   
   input b, c;
   output reg y;

   always @(*) begin
      y = b ^ c;
   end
endmodule

module C(/*AUTOARG*/
   x,
   clk, a, y
   );

   input clk;
   input a, y;
   output reg x;

   always @(posedge clk) begin
     x <= a & y;
   end
endmodule
```
> I just want to transform the module named "C" by running the following command:
```
verilator -Wall --sc --top-module C t_module_err.v
```
> But unfortunately, I meet a error like this:
```
%Warning-DECLFILENAME: t_module_err.v:1:8: Filename 't_module_err' does not match MODULE name: 't'
    1 | module t (
      |        ^
                       ... Use "/* verilator lint_off DECLFILENAME */" and lint_on around source to disable this message.
%Error: Specified --top-module 'C' isn't at the top level, it's under another cell 'A'
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s), 1 warning(s)
```
>  Is there any ways to solve it？
